laboratory_examinations.findings: Gallbladder distended with edematous wall up to 5 mm and slight surrounding pericholecystic fat stranding. Potential dense stone in gallbladder neck. Hyperemic liver parenchyma adjacent to gallbladder fossa, with normal liver parenchyma otherwise. Pneumobilia slightly increased from prior exam. Posterior pararenal fluid collection nearly completely resolved since the prior exam with mild residual thickening and stranding of paraspinal musculature posterior to the right kidney.
